    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Soviet Commissar for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_MVM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d286fn1">Sent to <persName corresp="#p_SSP1"
                            >Spalding</persName> at Moscow, via Navy channels, for delivery to
                            <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>, with the suggestion that
                            <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>’s reply be sent via
                            <persName corresp="#p_SSP1">Spalding</persName>. <persName
                            corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>’s reply is printed <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_424">p. 424</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-22">22 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British and ourselves are sending representatives from Cairo to Teheran
                    tomorrow, November 23, to make the physical arrangements for the Conference
                    including the living quarters and security in all details. It would be helpful
                    if you would advise our Commanding General in Teheran, General Con[n]olly, what
                    representative of the Soviet Government he should get in touch with to
                    coordinate our planning with yours. I would be grateful if you would also cable
                    me in Cairo that this has been arranged.</p>
                <p>I had a most hospitable welcome and interesting afternoon during our unexpected
                    stop in Stalingrad<note n="2" xml:id="d286fn2">The plane carrying <persName
                            corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName> and others from Moscow to Cairo
                        developed engine trouble and made an emergency landing at Stalingrad. See
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJR1">Deane</persName>, p. 35.</note> for which I
                    am very grateful.</p>
                <p>I look forward to seeing you. Regards.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
